In order to estimate the overall moderating effect of multiple biomarkers, Kraemer proposes a method for creating a ‘composite moderator’ from a weighted sum of moderating biomarkers [4, 6]. In the first step, a dataset is constructed from all possible pairwise combinations of treated and untreated subjects. From the parameterisation in Eq. 1, the change in outcome between the jth pair of treated (superscript T) and control (superscript C) subjects is equivalent to:
