A PTR uses biomarker values to recommend whether a patient should be treated or not. For example, statins are recommended in the UK if a person is aged over 40 and if their estimated CVD risk is at least 10% over a 10-year period [8]. Formally, this can be represented as: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
